<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Airlines Develops World Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The EAL has opened new flights to Tel Aviv of Israel, Beirut of
Lebanon and Bahrain while having resumed its flight to Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the EAL's flight to the United States has also
increased now to three times from twice a week one year ago, the
airlines said.
</P>
<P>
The EAl has leased two Boeing 767-300 passenger aircraft with a
view to providing its services efficiently.
</P>
<P>
The EAL obtained a 43.8 million birr (5.4 million U.S.
dollars) net profit during the last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The EAL, established 52 years ago, currently flies to 47
international destinations, out of which 25 are in Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
