<HEADLINE> Wang Nan Closer to Second Gold in Table Tennis (Updated) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EINDHOVEN, Netherlands, August 7 (Xinhua) -- World top pair Wang
Nan and Li Ju downed fellow Chinese Zhang Yining and Zhang Yingying in
straight sets at the women's doubles semifinals of the world table
tennis championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
World No. 1 ranked Wang, who earlier won the women's singles title
with a 3-2 victory over Zhang Yining, played coherently with No. 3 Li
Ju, beating the teenager pair 23-21, 21-17, 21-16.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yining is 17 and Zhang Yingying just 16.
</P>
<P>
Yang Ying and Sun Jin clinched the other final berth when they beat
South Korea's Park Hae Jung and Kim Moo Kyo 21-14, 21-9, 15-21, 21-18.
</P>
</TEXT>
