<HEADLINE> Over 17 Killed in Traffic Accident in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Police have identified on Saturday
five bodies of 17 people who were killed in a traffic accident
near Zambian capital city Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
The other 23 passengers injured in the same accident have been
identified and admitted in a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place Friday night, when a bus rammed into a
stationary truck and trailer at about 19:30 hours.
</P>
<P>
The impact was so great that all the seats on the left side
were cut through, resulting in deaths and injuries among
passengers.
</P>
<P>
July Danobo, owner of the ill-fated bus, said he could not
comment on the accident because he was still very shocked and
wanted to investigate what led to the accident.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, some of the victims were students,
they were bound for Lusaka from Kashikishi for holiday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
