<HEADLINE> S. African President in New Peace Bid on DRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki will meet his Ugandan, Tanzanian and Rwandan
counterparts Sunday to try to find peace for the Democratic
Republic of the Congo (DRC), South African Press Association
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda and Uganda are believed to be supporting Congolese
rebels fighting to topple embattled DRC President Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
A cease-fire agreement, brokered by Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba, was reached a month ago, but some rebel groups are yet to
sign the Lusaka accord.
</P>
<P>
Only the Congolese Liberation Movement, led by Jean-Pierre
Bemba signed the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday meeting would take place just six days before the
43rd Southern African Development Community (SADC) summit in
Mozambique, where peace in the region would also be discussed.
</P>
</TEXT>
