<HEADLINE> Tanzania Retires Corrupt Judge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has retired a
principle magistrate on charges of bribe and judicial misconduct,
the Judiciary Service Commission said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement released by the commission, the
decision to retire Principal Magistrate Boniface Warioba Magabe
was reached on July 16 after an investigation of his matter.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the magistrate has been retired in
public interest as he failed to observe legal ethics when
administering justice.
</P>
<P>
This is the latest judiciary scandal reported in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, a minister of state in the President's Office, Wilson
 Masilingi, told an International Conference on Moral Re-armament
in Dar es Salaam that Tanzania remains serious in fighting
corruption.  
</P>
</TEXT>
