<HEADLINE> Vajpayee Promises Powerful, Prosperous India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee said Sunday that the BJP will fulfill the Indian
people's dreams of "a powerful and prosperous India" in the new
millennium.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a public meeting in Ludhiana, Punjab to launch the
election campaign of the Akali-Dal-BJP alliance in the state, he
said the last general elections of the millennium would be held in
a "tough situation," according to the Press Trust of India.
</P>
<P>
The general elections are scheduled to be held in
September-October.
</P>
<P>
There was a need for all countrymen to make their contributions
towards the country's development, the process of which "will
start through the Loc Sabha (lower house of parliament) polls," he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said the the country's economy was in good health and
industrial production had increased, new houses were built, demand
for steel and cement grew, the foreign exchanges situation became
better and inflation came down to its lowest. "These are all base
points development."
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to voters country-wide to give a "clear
majority" to the BJP-led National Democratic Alliance in the
coming elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
