<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weather on Eclipse Day to Be Partially Good in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The weather condition on the
eclipse day on August 11 will be partially good in the northern
belt of France within which the sun will be completely covered by
the moon.
</P>
<P>
The northwest part of France will have a clear day, while the
northeast part of the country will remain cloudy, said the French
meteorological service, Meteo-France, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Meteo-France said that while in the northeast part of France
the condition of observation is expected to be no good, people can
see the rare celestial phenomenon in a perfect sunshine condition
in the northwest.
</P>
<P>
In the belt of eclipse, the day seems to be cloudy and a little
rainy first, but will start clearing up along the coast of English
Channel, in Bretagne, in Normandy, in Picardie and
Nord-Pas-de-Calais in the northwest in the morning, said
Meteo-France.
</P>
<P>
The complete eclipse will occur in the early afternoon for
about two minutes.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of tourists are expected to be flooding
into the belt on August 11 to witness the marriage between the Sun
and the Moon.
</P>
<P>
French traffic police will be on full alert during the day to
avoid accidents of all kinds.
</P>
<P>
The government has asked motorcyclists not to speed on the road
during the eclipse and not to ride the motors while wearing the
special sunglasses to be distributed free by the government on the
roads to protect the eyes of drivers and passengers.
</P>
<P>
The airports across France will provide enough security
precautions to the passengers on the planes arriving at the time
of the eclipse.
</P>
<P>
Psychoanalysts will also be mobilized on that day to take care
of their patients, who could be scared by the phenomenon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
