<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei Stepashin on Saturday
ordered the armed forces chief of staff and the Interior Ministry
forces chief to normalize the situation in the Dagestan republic,
the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The order came amid reports that about 500 armed Chechen
militants infiltrated into Dagestan early Saturday and trenched
near the villages of Ansalta and Rakhata in the mountainous
Botlikhsky district.
</P>
<P>
The armed Chechen group is believed to include Arabs and
people from Central Asia, Tass quoted the Dagestani interior
ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is moving its forces to the Botlikhsky district
and ascertaining intents of the Chechen guerrillas, Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
Recent weeks have witnessed a number of skirmishes along the
borders between Dagestan and the neighboring republic of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
At least 14 people were killed in shoot-outs between heavily
armed gangs and Russian security forces near the border on Monday
and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Russian officials said earlier that the attackers were based
in Chechnya and get into Russia through the mountains.
</P>
<P>
Since then, as many as 150 fighters have occupied a Dagestani
village near the border. (Russia-Dagestan-Situation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- S. Leone's former rebel leader Foday Sankoh has said
in Togo's capital Lome that he had ordered a group of former junta
soldiers to free the hostages held by rebel faction loyal to
Johnny Koromah.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not worried," he said. "The position of the high command
is that this has no effect on the peace accord," said the leader
of the Revolutionary United Front(RUF) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 30 U.N. employees, aid workers, west African intervention
force soldiers and journalists are currently held in the Okra
Hills, some 65 km outside Freetown, capital of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The RUF leader said the kidnapping was an "isolated" incident
that did not signal a broader split in the rebels' alliance with
Sierra Leone's former military junta and noted that he had ordered
the soldiers to release their captives.
</P>
<P>
He also accused officials of United Nations and West African
Peacekeeping Force, ECOMOG, of carelessly provoking the crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said they had failed to contact senior rebel officials
before sending the delegation into rebel-held territory.
</P>
<P>
The kidnap took place when an international delegation met with
junta soldiers, who had said they would free about 150 women and
children captured during the war.
</P>
<P>
The junta soldiers freed several captives Thursday, which
included two U. N. officials, a Reuters reporter and a clergy man,
requiring them to convey their demand for food, medicine among
others. (SLeone-Rebel-Hostages)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian Congress President Sonia Gandhi Saturday
launched her party's election campaign in Jharsuguda, Orissa,
promising to provide a stable government for the full five-year
term, Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
She said the BJP government had "compromised" India's security
and the nation's image had "plummeted" in the world.
</P>
<P>
She urged the people to bring to an end the series of weak
governments at the center.
</P>
<P>
She said she had entered politics not because of lust for power
but because of her concern for the poor, down-trodden and backward
people and the country's image abroad.
</P>
<P>
She said the performance of the BJP-led government during the
last 16 months showed that such parties grabbed power just to "
satiate" their own self interest.
</P>
<P>
Prime minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee is scheduled to launch the
BJP's election campaign Sunday. (India-Sonia-Election Campaign)
</P>
</TEXT>
