<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- A Turkish trade union leader was assassinated late
Friday night in northern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a man identified as Cengiz Balik opened
fire at Semsi Denizer, Secretary-General of the Turk-Labor Trade
Union and Chairman of the Mining-Labor Trade Union, in front of
Denizer's home at Site Semti Bahcelievler district of Zonguldak
province. (BC-Turkey-Assassination)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- A Sri Lankan maid working here in a Kuwaiti
family was beaten and tortured to death by her employer, local
newspapers reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The woman, who was not named, was pronounced dead by a
physician urgently called in to treat her.
</P>
<P>
The doctor immediately reported the incident, which took place
in downtown Kuwait, to the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The police have detained the Kuwaiti couple allegedly
responsible for the death of the Sri Lankan woman.
(BC-Kuwait-Maid-Torture)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- The Dead Sea, the saltiest body of water on earth and
world-renowned tourist resort, is shrinking at an alarming rate
and might disappear in 20-25 years, Jordan Times reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Landlocked in the Jordan Valley between Israel and Jordan, the
Dead Sea has shrunk to around 50 kilometers in length from 80
kilometers three decades ago due to drought, pollution and over
exploitation, the paper said. (BC-Jordan-Dead Sea)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq on Saturday refuted the U.S claim that the
U.S.-British warplanes have carried out raids against Iraqi
targets in the no-fly zones in response to Iraqi provocations,
calling them "sheer lies."
</P>
<P>
In a statement carried by the Iraqi News Agency, Iraqi Air
Defense Commander Shaheen Yassin Mohammed said the claimed 108 air
raids by U.S.-British warplanes against Iraqi targets since last
December were not for monitoring the no-fly zones but for
aggression against Iraq's sovereignty and territorial integrity.
(BC-Iraq-US Claim) 
</P>
