<HEADLINE> Ethnic Clashes Burst in Northern Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Fierce shootouts burst Saturday
morning in Northen Kosovo between Albanians and Serbs, the
Albanian Telegraphic Agency (ATA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The shootouts took place at 10 a.m. near a bridge which divides
the city in two parts, when thousands of Albanians tried to pass
the bridge and were stopped by Serbs, the Albanian news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The KFOR (NATO forces in Kosovo) had intervened with the
support of tanks, but failed to stop the clashes, it said.
</P>
<P>
The casualties of the clashes remained unknown so far. The ATA
said that shooting from the Serb-controled northern part of the
city could be heard over the past three nights. 
</P>
