<HEADLINE> Chinese President Writes Inscription for Locomotive Plant Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin has written
an inscription to mark the 100th anniversary of the Dalian
Locomotive Plant.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's inscription reads "More efforts should be made to
develop China's locomotive industry so as to meet domestic needs
and export more."
</P>
<P>
The plant, founded in 1899, has developed 30 types of
locomotives and has manufactured nearly 5,000 locomotives since
New China was founded in 1949. These accounted for 40 percent of
the country's total locomotive output.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, the plant began to export locomotives and has by now
exported more than 80 locomotives, which account for 80 percent of
the country's diesel locomotive exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
