<HEADLINE> Xinhua Photo List for August 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 8 (Xinhua)-- Following is the photo list for
August 8 released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
1. The elders enjoy themselves at the First Chorus Festival for
the Aged held in Beijing. Over 3,000 performers from about 60
choruses sang 16 songs for an audience of nearly 10,000.
</P>
<P>
2. A policeman checks publications of the Falun Gong cult in
Huhhot. The regional government has destroyed about 30,000 books,
2,000 portraits of Li Hongzhi and 800 video tapes on the banned
cult.
</P>
<P>
3. Two police officers check the books on Falun Gong cult with
the help of local residents in Harbin. In the process of banning
the cult, Heilongjiang provincial government received wide
cooperation and help from the localities.
</P>
<P>
4. Piles of publications of Falun Gong cult are ready for
burning in Jinan. The provincial government has seized about 310,
000 books and video tapes on the banned cult.
</P>
<P>
5. Girls of the Shui ethnic group rehearse a traditional dance
for the national Minority Games in Guizhou. The games is to open
in Lhasa this month. Competitors from the ethnic minorities will
show their ethnic sports during the games.
</P>
<P>
6. Two performers of Bouyei ethnic group rehearse the
traditional sports dancing "shoulder pole" at the Guiyang Stadium.
The dance will be put on show in front of the Potala Palace in
Lhasa during the national Minority Games.
</P>
<P>
7. Fu Jianye, a 77-year-old retiree, studies English at home as
his wife does cleaning in Guiyang. Fu got his bachelor degree last
year and he is trying to get the master degree on contemporary
literature from the Xinan Normal University.
</P>
<P>
8. Two fortune-tellers entertain themselves by listening to a
radio at the downtown street of Shijiazhuang. As more and more
people believe in science instead of superstition, fewer and fewer
local residents go to the fortune-tellers. Mr. Wang (R) has not
had even a single deal for the whole morning.
</P>
<P>
9. Picture shows the newly-completed Shanghai International
Conference Center against the Oriental Pear TV tower in Shanghai.
The center, built with a total investment of 100 million dollars,
is comprised of a huge banquet hall and 30 meeting rooms. The 1999
global forum of Fortune will be hosted here in September.
</P>
<P>
10. Performers of Shanxi Cadre Chorus sing the song "I love you
China" in the opening ceremony of Tour Festival of Heng Mountain.
The officials of Shanxi Province hope the festival would help
promote Shanxi's tourism industry.  
</P>
