<HEADLINE> Qatar's Emir Visits Lebanon to Promote Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Qatar's Emir Hamad Bin Khalifa Al
Thani Sunday arrived here for a three-day state visit for talks
on the Middle East peace process and bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari emir is the first head of state to come to Lebanon
since Lebanese President Emile Lahoud took office last November.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon is Thani's second stop on a regional tour that has
taken him first to the Palestinian self-rule area earlier on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Lahoud personally received Thani at Beirut's International
Airport.
</P>
<P>
Thani will hold talks with Lahoud, House Speaker Nabih Berri
and Prime Minister Salim Hoss on the widely expected resumption of
peace talks in the region and bilateral ties. 
