<HEADLINE> Cote d'Ivoire Qualify for All-Africa Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Cote d'Ivoire have booked
the last berth for the next month's All-Africa Games football
tournament in South Africa by topping in Zone three.
</P>
<P>
The Ivorians join Algeria, Cameroon, Mali, Mauritius, Uganda,
Zambia and the hosts South Africa at the eight-nation competition
after a goalless draw with Ghana.
</P>
<P>
Both teams finished the group, which features Nigeria, Burkina
Faso and the two teams, on five points, but Cote d'Ivorie edged
off Ghana on goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria collected two points from two draws and one loss in the
three-round qualifying competition, while Burkina Faso finished at
the bottom of the standings with two points. 
</P>
