<HEADLINE> CPPCC Leader Meets With Chinese Outstanding Youth Program Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of
the national committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), met here today with a China
Synergy Program for Outstanding Youth delegation at Beijing's
Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Wang told them that 1999 is an important year in Chinese
history because it will celebrate the 50th anniversary of the
founding of new China and the return of Macao to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The country has witnessed great changes in the half century,
particularly in the two decades of reform and opening, he said,
with the standard of living improving a great deal and the overall
strength of the country increasing.
</P>
<P>
The cohesiveness of all the ethnic groups in China is a major
force in these achievements, he said, and compatriots from Hong
Kong and Macao and other overseas Chinese have made their
contributions and he believes that China will become even stronger
and more prosperous in the next century with their support.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was headed by Chang Hsin-kang, and had Zou Zhe
Kai, Leo Tung-Hai Lee, and S.K. Chan as advisors. It consisted of
73 Chinese studying in Hong Kong and abroad.  
