<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Speaks About Three Emphases On Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, the chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), told a recent meeting that all CPPCC
departments need to implement the spirit of the "three emphases"
on education.
</P>
<P>
Li told the meeting, which was on CPPCC departments carrying
out the important decision of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party, to focus on theoretical studies, political
awareness, and healthy conduct.
</P>
<P>
The fundamental reason the Chinese Communist Party won one
victory after another during both wartime and peaceful period was
that the Party often listened to and accepted the opinions and
supervision of the people and was courageous enough to carry out
critricism and self-criticism and to continue to overcome
shortcomings, he said.
</P>
<P>
He warned, however, that some Party officials have not been
doing very well in these respects these days and have forgotten
the Party's fine tradition and work style. He asked officials at
all levels to take the lead in the education campaign to improve
work performance and to solve some major problems by relying on
the people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
