LONDON -- The Irish National Liberation Army (INLA) has become
the first paramilitary group in Northern Ireland to declare its
war is over, according to a newspaper report.
</P>
<P>
The INLA, which came to prominence in 1979 when it killed
Conservative MP Airey Neave in a car bomb, has told its political
wing, the Irish Republican Socialist Party (IRSP), it has no
reason to continue its armed campaign, The Sunday Times reported.
(INLA-War-Over)
</P>
