<DOCNO> XIE19990808.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Member Denounces Falun Gong Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Liu Shuwen, a female deputy-head
of a Falun Gong training center in Beijing, says that Li Hongzhi,
the founder of Falun Gong, deceived innocent people with his
fallacies and urged them to oppose the government.
</P>
<P>
Liu, 61, was a senior engineer at a factory in aerospace
industry when she retired and began to practice Falun Gong in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Liu was appointed deputy-head of the training center at the end
of 1998. She said that the illegal gatherings at the Beijing TV
station and at Zhongnanhai, the site of the central government, by
Falun Gong cult members were, in fact, orchestrated by Li Hongzhi
behind the scenes.
</P>
<P>
She recalled that a meeting was convened by the Beijing Falun
Gong training center on the morning of April 24 at which two
senior officials of the Falun Dafa Research Society, the
governing body of Falun Gong, asked all Falun Gong practitioners
to go to Zhongnanhai.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that the cult's trick is never to say directly that a
person must do something but all practitioners have to do what is
asked of them and are asked to strive for an 'enlightenment'
advocated by Li Hongzhi or they won't be perfect in their practice.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi often sent orders to practitioners in the form of
sutras and if anyone went against his will he would issue a sutra
to force the person to correct this, according to Liu.
</P>
<P>
When she saw through the true nature and the pernicious effects
of Falun Gong, Liu vowed to leave Falun Gong and was determined to
persuade other practitioners to do the same.  
</P>
