<HEADLINE> Manila Landslide Death Toll Rises to 46 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from a landslide
that hit Cherry Hill Subdivision in Antipolo, Manila, reached 46
on Sunday afternoon, with over 20 others still missing.
</P>
<P>
Army Gen. Nestor Castillo, commander of the rescue force, told
reporters that rescuers recovered nine more bodies Sunday, but
seven of them had yet to be identified.
</P>
<P>
They included three boys, a girl and three old men, he said.
</P>
<P>
The rescue and retrieval operations have been accelerated and
will continue until all houses demolished in the landslide Tuesday
night have been searched, the general said.
</P>
<P>
A series of landslides and heavy flooding in the Philippine
capital of Manila and nearby provinces in the past week killed at
least 118 people, according to the National Disaster Coordination
Council. 
</P>
