<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qatari Emir Visits Palestinian Self-rule Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Emir of Qatar Sheikh Hamad Bin
Khalifa al-Thani arrived Sunday at Gaza Airport for an official
visit to the Palestinian territories, the first of its kind by a
Gulf leader.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted upon arrival by Chairman of the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) Yasser Arafat, senior Palestinian
officials and some accredited envoys of foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Arafat and Sheikh Hamad are scheduled to hold talks on issues
of mutual concern, particularly the Middle East peace process and
bilateral economic cooperation as well as Qatar's financial
support to the PNA.
</P>
<P>
Local news media said that the Qatari emir may donate his
private plane to the PNA to boost its airliners which are few in
number.
</P>
<P>
Qatar opened a representation office in Gaza in November 1995
and it has granted 5 million U.S. dollars to the Palestinian
authorities since 1994.
</P>
<P>
Also, Qatar has initiated one flight a week between Gaza and
Doha after the inauguration of the Gaza Airport at the end of last
year. 
</P>
