<HEADLINE> Ma Lin Beats Waldner in Singles Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EINDHOVEN, Netherlands, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ma Lin
outlasted two-time world champion Jan-Ove Waldner in the men's singles
semifinals of the world table tennis championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The set scores were 18-21, 14-21, 21-19, 21-19, 21-17.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old Swede, the only player in the world to have won a
"Grand Slam" of the Olympic, world championship and World Cup titles,
used his deceptive serves and follow-up topspin strokes to clinch the
first two sets easily.
</P>
<P>
Ma came back strongly, unleashing a string of devastating forehand
attacks to win three sets in a row, while Walnder looked nervous and
missed quite a few easy kills.
</P>
<P>
Late Sunday, Ma Lin will vie for the crown with the winner of the
game between Olympic champion Liu Guoliang and Austrian Werner
Schlager.
</P>
<P>
Liu said earlier that he could win the title if he reached the
semifinals. 
</P>
