<HEADLINE> Croatia Beats Burkina Faso in Soccer Opener at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Croatia beat Burkina Faso
1-0 in the opening game in group A of the soccer tournament in
Siska at the Military World Games Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
After the goalless first half, Renato Piliovic scored the
winning goal four minutes after break, blasting the ball past
Burkina Faso goalie Mathieu Traore into the net from left in the
penalty box.
</P>
<P>
Burkina Faso's best chance came in the first half, when Boka
Bonebo's powerful blast was parried off by Croatian keeper
Zankarlo Simunic.
</P>
<P>
In the other group A game played in Zagreb, Mohamed Abdelnaser
scored a double as Egypt whitewashed Ukraine 5-0.
</P>
<P>
The goals from Abdelnaser and Fathy Sherif Basuonyabdel Hamid
gave the Egyptians a 2-0 lead before break.
</P>
<P>
Abdelahmid and Abdalahabdel Hamip Ahmed then each scored once
before Abdelnaser netted his second in the dying minutes to seal
the victory.
</P>
<P>
In group B, Greece drubbed the United States 7-0 while Germany
beat Guinea 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Eight teams are competing in two groups in the preliminary
stage, which kicked off one day before the opening ceremony on
Sunday. 
</P>
