<HEADLINE> Insiders Criticize Falun Gong Sect (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- With the official ban on Falun
Gong on July 22, officials with the sect have discarded the Falun
Gong and came to recognize the true nature and motives of this
illegal organization.
</P>
<P>
Duan Rongxin, a former head of the Falun Gong general training
center in Shijiazhuang, capital of north China's Hebei province,
exposed the sect as an anti-governmental organization under
absolute control of Li Hongzhi, founder of the Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
"Li Hongzhi has advocated truthfulness, benevolence and
tolerance among his followers, actually he was only using these
banners to disguise his ulterior political motives," said Duan,
who has broken away from the Falun Gong sect and discarded the
Falun Gong practice since the government ban on the sect.
</P>
<P>
Duan, a 39-year-old official with a real estate company, was
appointed by Li Hongzhi in 1994 as the head of the general
training center in Shijiazhuang, and was responsible for operation
of four subordinate centers in the province.
</P>
<P>
Duan said the seemingly loosely controlled Falun Gong sect is
actually a highly-organized sect under absolute control of the
supreme leader Li Hongzhi, who sends his orders through the
Research Society of Falun Dafa to the general training centers,
thereby to subordinate branches.
</P>
<P>
"Any Falun Gong official who did not follow Li Hongzhi's orders
was immediately dismissed and widely condemned inside the
organization," Duan said.
</P>
</TEXT>
