<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Rallies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai stock market
resumed the rally since May 19 after weeks of correction,
triggered by a series of favorable government policies and
increasing trade volume.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics from the Shanghai Stock Exchange showed
the composite index closed at 1,646.59 Friday, a rise of 2.82
percent over the previous week. Of the 452 Class-A shares on the
market, 306 shares have seen prices going up.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume of the stock market expanded moderately by nearly
16 billion yuan to 61.09 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao Beer became the most traded stock with more than 90
percent of the shares changing hands during the week, while Huazi
Industry led all stocks in price gains.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts said the main reason behind the market rally
was that the government has recently announced a series of
measures to support the market, which include a circular from the
China Securities Regulatory Commission calling for better forms of
initial public offering of stocks, and a central bank announcement
to allow securities brokerages to enter the inter-bank money
market and bond buyback market for more financing.
</P>
<P>
However, index of the B share market, which is restricted to
overseas investors, lost 3.98 percent to 45.64 points in the week.
</P>
<P>
The funds market reported a turnover of 2.93 billion yuan,
almost the same as that of the previous week. Of the total of 23
funds, ten funds saw prices edge up.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the bonds market shrank by nearly four billion yuan
to 27.21 billion yuan during the period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
