<HEADLINE> Zambian-Israeli Friendship Association Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Zambia and Israel have set up a
friendship association to foster relationship between the two
countries, Zambian Sunday Mail newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
The association is spearheaded by the Zambians who have studied
in Israel and the Israelis at the Center for International
Cooperation in the Israeli Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Lusaka Mayor Patricia Nawa as saying Saturday
at the launch of the Shalom Club here that the formation of the
association will help cement the friendship which already exists
between the two governments.
</P>
<P>
"The formation of this club is a very important ingredient
between the Zambian government and the State of Israel," said the
mayor.
</P>
<P>
She said the establishment of the Shalom Club was also
important because it would help the returning students to
integrate their skills into national development programs for the
benefit of the Zambian community.
</P>
<P>
The association will also help facilitate and organize local
courses in various disciplines by inviting Israeli experts to come
and lecture.
</P>
<P>
"The initiative of organizing and facilitating local courses
will go a long way as this will increase the number of trainees
while at the same time reducing the costs of travel, lodging and
tuition," Nawa said.
</P>
<P>
She said it was important to promote technical, cultural and
economic cooperation between the two countries through training as
this was vital for a country like Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
