<HEADLINE> Leading Insurer Meets Premium Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- China Pacific Insurance Co. Ltd,
the only Shanghai-based national insurer, has seen its premium
income rise a year-on-year 13.1 percent to 7.02 billion yuan
during the first six months of this year, meeting 52.22 percent of
the annual premium target.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, life insurance premium rose 7.38 percent over the
same 1998 period to 3.154 billion yuan, while premium from life
insurance soared 20.85 percent to 3.865 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Company officials told Xinhua that China Pacific Insurance has
striven to optimize the structure of its insurance products,
improve service and management on redemption, and reduce cost to
survive the heated market competition.
</P>
<P>
The company has also managed to achieve profit growth after
paying nine million U.S. dollars in redemption for a ship-sinking
accident and nearly 100 million yuan for summer flooding in
central and eastern China.
</P>
<P>
As one of the nation's leading joint-stock insurance companies,
Shanghai Pacific Insurance has more than 400 branches at home and
abroad, and the total assets insured by the company were valued at
3.803 trillion yuan in 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
