<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Drops to 1.19 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The country's annual inflation
rate continued its free fall and dropped to a record low of 1.19
percent for the week ended July 24, the Reserve Bank of India said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The rate of increase in prices, based on Wholesale Price Index
(WPI), fell by 0.43 percentage points during the week to 1.19
percent (provisional) from 1.62 percent (provisional) the week
before.
</P>
<P>
During the same period last year, inflation rate was higher at
8.78 percent mainly on account of an upsurge in food prices due to
lower production.
</P>
<P>
The sharp fall in inflation is mainly on account of a higher
base last year due to higher prices of food articles, especially
vegetables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
