<HEADLINE> Sixty Chinese Start From Canada on Arctic Adventure Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A group of 60 Chinese from the
mainland of China, Hong Kong, Taiwan and North America launched a
tour of adventure to the Arctic from the Canadian western city of
Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
Local media said Saturday that the tourists would spend two
weeks from August 6 to 19 to signify solidarity among the Chinese
the world over.
</P>
<P>
They were scheduled to be convoyed by 16 vehicles through
British Columbia and Yukon Territory until reaching Inuvik of
Northwest Territories on August 12.
</P>
<P>
From there, they would take a plane to Tuktoyaktuk, where they
are expected to board a scientific survey ship from the People's
Republic of China, joining 120 Chinese scientists in celebration
of the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The 8,000-kilometer tour is sponsored by a fishing association
of Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
