<HEADLINE> Heavy Industrial City Hosts Int'l Exchange Events </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning province, is expected to hold a series of
international exchange activities in the upcoming three months.
</P>
<P>
As a traditional heavy industrial city in northeast China,
Shenyang has developed itself into the economic and cultural
center in the region. This is the first time for the city to hold
international events of such a large scale and high standard.
</P>
<P>
The events will cover three areas: modern agriculture and
industry, trade and culture, featuring a series of expositions on
floral products, vegetables, automobiles, power technology and
equipment, cosmetics and hairdressing articles, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Also included are international trade talks, a commodities fair,
a multinational forum, a computer software festival, and two
international seminars on material science and urban environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
A series of cultural exchange events will also be held in the
city, including a theatrical art festival, a film festival, an
international music festival, a festival of chess and cards, and a
fashion show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
