<HEADLINE> North China Port City Attracts Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin
Municipality has become a hot attraction to overseas tourists, and
their arrivals increased a year-on-year five percent to 128,000
during the first half year period.
</P>
<P>
Increasing visitors on business trips gave a strong boost to
the tourism sector of the city. As the largest port city in north
China, Tianjin has marine routes linking it with more than 170
countries and regions, and is home to over 10,000 overseas-funded
ventures. Arrivals of overseas visitors on business soared during
the past several years to 200,000 last year.
</P>
<P>
The various sites of historical interests and natural scenes
hold strong appeal to overseas tourists, while trips to the
villages to experience the life of the farmers also attracted
large numbers of overseas tourists.
</P>
<P>
To better cater to the tourists, the city has developed 37
tourist spots, opened 170 travel agencies, and built 78 hotels.
</P>
</TEXT>
