will travel to Laos on Tuesday to hold talks with the Lao
government and agencies concerned about the suspension of the
project.
</P>
<P>
According to Gun, a study by the firm found the current
situation was not good for investment in the railway project, as
demand for train services was 40 percent below earlier estimates.
</P>
<P>
