<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Croatia has begun the legal
proceedings which will lead to the hand-over of a former senior
Croatian officer wanted by the International War Criminal Tribunal
for the former Yugoslavia, Justice Minister Zvonimir Separovic
said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Separovic, quoted by the Croatian State Television, said that
the hand-over of Vinko Martinovic and other war suspects was a
complicated legal issue since the charges against them raised by
the country's judicial authorities and the criminal tribunal were
not totally the same.
</P>
