criminal suspects sought by the tribunal in The Hague set up by
the United Nations after the five-year Bosnian war in the early
1990s. Martinovic was charged with ethnic cleansing during the war,
and the tribunal late last year demanded Croatia hand over him.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation with the tribunal is a precondition set by the West
for Croatia to gain membership of the European Union and NATO.
