<HEADLINE> Johansson Reaches Canadian Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Thomas Johansson advanced
to the final of the Candadian Open in Montreal on Saturday by
beating Germany's Nicolas Kiefer 4-6, 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Johansson, seeded 11th, will play the winner of the second
semifinal between second-seeded Andre Agassi of the United States
and second-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals, Johansson came in fresh following an early
match the day before, while Kiefer was still recovering from a
late-night, three-set victory over top-seeded Patrick Rafter of
Australia.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer held service to open the second set, but then lost nine
consecutive games.
</P>
<P>
The German's first serve deserted him and he was no match for
Johansson, a dogged baseline player in the Swedish tradition, in
the long rallies on his second serve. 
</P>
