<HEADLINE> Ethnic Clashes Burst in Northern Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Fierce shoot-outs burst Saturday
morning in northern Kosovo between ethnic Albanians and Serbs, the
Albanian Telegraphic Agency (ATA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The shoot-outs started at 10 a.m. local time (0800 GMT) near a
bridge which divides the city in two parts, when thousands of
Albanians tried to pass the bridge and were stopped by Serbs, the
Albanian news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The KFOR (UN peacekeeping force in Kosovo) had intervened with
the support of tanks, but failed to stop the clashes, it said.
</P>
<P>
The casualties of the clashes remained unknown so far. 
</P>
