<HEADLINE> Steady Growth In Southern China's Private Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 8 (xinhua) -- The private economy of south
China's Guangdong Province has been growing since the beginning of
the year, according to local official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Administration for Industry and Commerce reports
that, by the end of June, there were 1.54 million households
involved in industry and commerce and more than 150,000 other
private businesses, a 2.2 percent and 6.3 percent increase,
respectively. They employ some 4.89 million people, an increase of
3.6 percent from the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Aggregate registered capital of these private businesses
amounts to 14.42 billion yuan, up 7.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Industrial and commercial households and other private
businesses now provide a wider range of services in information,
computers, software development, home economics, education,
medical care, and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
About 87 percent of the province's new private businesses this
year are in the service sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
