<HEADLINE> China to Issue Stamps Featuring Ethnic Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 8 (Xinhua) -- China's General Post Office is to
issue a set of stamps next March featuring the landscapes of the
Dali Bai Autonomous Prefecture in southwest China's Yunnan
Province.
</P>
<P>
Dali, located in the northwestern part of the province, is one
of the country's most famous scenic attractions.
</P>
<P>
With rich cultural relics, colorful folk customs, unique ethnic
traditions, numerous religious temples and historical artistic
grottoes, the prefecture is a mecca for tourists worldwide. In the
first half of this year, it received 2.53 million domestic and
overseas visitors, of whom nearly 40,000 are overseas travelers.
</P>
<P>
The stamps will make the prefecture better known globally, said
a local official, explaining that the issue is part of a tourism
promotion drive for Dali.  
