<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Macao Air Route Prospers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Over the past twelve months,
more than 30,000 passengers have been transported from this, the
largest industrial and commerical center in the Chinese inland
areas, to Macao by 240 scheduled flights on a regular air route.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Airlines opened the route on August 2, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Airlines is the inland areas' sole air company which
has the right to operate flights between Shanghai and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The company pays special attention to giving convenience and
help to the handicapped, the elderly and overseas passengers.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the stewards have prepared a diversified food
menu to cater to the preferences of passengers from Macao, Taiwan
and Hong Kong regions.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the air ticket reservation rate on this route has
been kept at a record of over 85 percent. 
