<HEADLINE> Myanmar Produces 333,500 Tons of Cement in 1998-99 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar produced a total of
333,513 tons of cement in fiscal 1998-99, which ended in March,
149,929 tons less than that in the previous fiscal year, according
to the latest Economic Indicators published by the country's
Central Statistical Organization.
</P>
<P>
Cement has become more and more in demand in Myanmar day by day
as the country geared up its pace in recent years in building
infrastructural facilities including motor roads and bridges.
</P>
<P>
In 1998-99, Myanmar imported 65.55 million U.S. dollars worth
of cement, while in 1997-98, the cement it bought was valued at
83.76 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In order to meet domestic demand, Myanmar planned to build a
large-scale cement factory at a cost of 150 million dollars to
produce 4,000 tons of cement daily. 
</P>
