<HEADLINE> Shanghai's State Advertising Firms Sluggish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 8 (Xinhua) -- The State-owned advertising
companies in China's financial and commemrical center, Shangahi,
are lagging far behind their private and overseas-funded
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, State-owned advertising firms
saw their combined revenues drop 34 million yuan, or about 3
percent, from the same period last year, according to the city's
industrial and commercial administration.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded advertising firms on the other hand saw
revenues rise 9 percent and private firms saw revenues go up 28
percent.
</P>
