<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 people including
five women were injured Saturday when two express trains collided
in Pakistan's central Sindh province.
</P>
<P>
According to railway officials, the incident took place at
about 19:25 local time (14:25 GMT) when an express train dashed
into another near Latifabad railway crossing, about one kilometer
from Hyderabad railway junction.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers, who rushed to the spot along with ambulances,
said that at least 17 persons, who were on board in the last
carriage of Mehran Express, received injuries when the engine of
Zakaria Express dashed against it.
</P>
<P>
The railway officials said that the incident could have caused
heavy casualties if the driver of Zakaria Express had not applied
the brakes timely.
</P>
<P>
They said that they heard a high noise of the brakes and a bang
of collision.
</P>
<P>
A railway employee said that the cause of the accident could be
negligence of the cabin of Train Despatcher's Office. 
</P>
